{
  "texts": [
    "More benchmarks such as Gerbil should be constructed to provide this reliable comparison among frameworks.Finally, we observed that the latest tendency regarding entity linking is to apply it to medical data where there are events that trigger a sudden increase in the number of publications, such as the COVID-19 pandemic.",
    "For instance, PubMed added new 952,919 citations only in 2020.",
    "In this context, new word embedding models (such as BioBERT [97], PubMedBERT [64] and SciBERT [18]) are pre-trained on large biomedical corpora through unsupervised tasks and then fine-tuned [65,66] for specific tasks, including EL.",
    "These models achieved state-of-the-art performance in several EL benchmarks [150].Fig. 1 Fig.",
    "1 Named entity recognition example Fig. 44Fig."
  ]
}